%p
  I’m looking into
  %a{ :href => "http://git.or.cz/" }
    git
  as an alternative to subversion.
%p
  As most of my servers use a non-standard port for sshd I was interested in trying out git-1.5.3.x for it’s support for ssh://name@host:port/ but ubuntu gutsy only had 1.5.2.5 available so off to #git I went:
%p
  For Ubuntu Gutsy:
%ol
  %li
    apt-get install devscripts fakeroot
  %li
    dget -x http://ftp.debian.org/debian/pool/main/g/git-core/git-core_1.5.3.5-1.dsc
  %li
    cd git-core-1.5.3.5
  %li
    apt-get build-dep git-core
  %li
    dpkg-buildpackage -rfakeroot -us -uc
%p
  %del
    For Ubuntu Dapper
  \:
%p
  %strong
    Update
  \: Apparently the version of dpkg-buildpackage that comes with dapper is too old, so in the end I upgraded Dapper &gt; Edgy &gt; Feisty &gt; Gutsy
%ol
  %li
    %del
      apt-get install devscripts fakeroot
  %li
    %del
      wget http://www.backports.org/debian/pool/main/g/git-core/git-core_1.5.3.4-1
      %sub
        bpo40+1.dsc (as dget doesn’t exist in devscripts on dapper)
  %li
    %del
      wget http://www.backports.org/debian/pool/main/g/git-core/git-core_1.5.3.4-1
      bpo40+1.diff.gz
  %li
    %del
      wget http://www.backports.org/debian/pool/main/g/git-core/git-core_1.5.3.4.orig.tar.gz
  %li
    %del
      dpkg-source -x git-core_1.5.3.4-1~bpo40+1.dsc
  %li
    %del
      cd git-core-1.5.3.4
  %li
    %del
      apt-get build-dep git-core
  %li
    %del
      dpkg-buildpackage -rfakeroot -us -uc
%p
  %del
    (You may need to manually install libsvn-core-perl && tcl8.4 )
